Sentencas: La0.8Sr0.2MnO3-delta (LSM) and LSM-8 mol% yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) composite cathodes were fabricated using electrostatic spray assisted vapour deposition (ESAVD) method.
Titulo: The electrochemical properties of LSM-based cathodes fabricated by electrostatic spray assisted vapour deposition

Sentencas: The porous cathode layers of LSM and LSM-YSZ with high specific surface areas were obtained by optimizing the deposition parameters.
Titulo: The electrochemical properties of LSM-based cathodes fabricated by electrostatic spray assisted vapour deposition

Sentencas: It was found that the introduction of YSZ into LSM decreased the electrochemical impedance significantly.
Titulo: The electrochemical properties of LSM-based cathodes fabricated by electrostatic spray assisted vapour deposition

Sentencas: The activation effect of passing current on the electrochemical activity of the LSM-YSZ composite cathodes was much lower than that of the LSM cathodes.
Titulo: The electrochemical properties of LSM-based cathodes fabricated by electrostatic spray assisted vapour deposition

Sentencas: For the LSM-YSZ composite cathodes, there was a saturation of current with increasing applied potential at higher temperatures (from 900 to 1000 degrees C).
Titulo: The electrochemical properties of LSM-based cathodes fabricated by electrostatic spray assisted vapour deposition

Sentencas: The LSM-YSZ composite cathode fabricated by ESAVD exhibited high electrochemical activity at high and intermediate temperatures (from 800 to 1000 degrees C).
Titulo: The electrochemical properties of LSM-based cathodes fabricated by electrostatic spray assisted vapour deposition

Sentencas: This suggests that ESAVD is a promising technique for the fabrication of solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathodes.
Titulo: The electrochemical properties of LSM-based cathodes fabricated by electrostatic spray assisted vapour deposition
